{
  "doc_id": "30427",
  "text": "Solving analogy questions for diagrams and sketches has been extensively explored in AI [CITATION_1] . These papers either assume simple forms of drawings [CITATION_2] , require an abstract representation of diagrams [CITATION_3] , or spatial reasoning [CITATION_4] . In [CITATION_5] an analogy-based framework is proposed to learn 'image filters' between a pair of images to creat an 'analogous' filtered result on a third image. Related to analogies is learning how to separate category and style properties in images, which has been studied using bilinear models [CITATION_6] . In this paper, we study the problem of visual analogies for natural images possessing different semantic properties where obtaining abstract representations is extremely challenging.",
